      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Pattern reuse",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "Before copying a pattern from a reference (another system, a precedent, a textbook), identify the source-context constraint that made the pattern load-bearing there. Test whether that constraint applies in this system. If it doesn't, either reframe what the pattern does here or don't transfer it. The lens cuts both ways — sometimes the pattern should transfer MORE than instinct says (shedding source-specific heavy machinery), not less."
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-22",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "all-phases"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Reasoning under pushback",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "When the operator questions a concern you raised, defend it with reasoning or reframe to the underlying structural concern. Withdraw only if your concern is genuinely unfounded. \"Are you sure?\" is a question about confidence + quality + correctness, NOT a request to pivot."
      },
      "target_hooks": [
        {
          "target": "agents/qa_agent_prompt.md",
          "hook_type": "agent_prompt_line",
          "text": "Governed by operating principle OP-22 — see quality/rules_library.md."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-23",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "all-phases"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Verification",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "Before making a comparative claim (\"this is better\", \"this is missing\", \"X is consistent with Y\"), read the source directly. Cheap verification beats one wrong claim. If you can't verify in scope, say so explicitly."
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-24",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "all-phases"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
