    {
      "cell_id": "OP-28",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "all-phases"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Estimation",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "Calibrate estimates against observed prior work — not against speculative resource-overflow concerns. When a task estimate is uncertain, do the smallest tractable bite first and re-estimate from actual usage. (The specific over-estimation magnitude varies by operator-system; calibrate locally rather than copying a fixed multiplier.)"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-29",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "define+build",
        "refactor-existing"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Dependency analysis",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "When the conclusion is \"X depends on Y resolving\", also ask \"does Y depend on X being in a better state?\" Audit both edges before locking the sequence; if there's a cycle, surface it for the operator."
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-30",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "define+build"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Controls",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "When a blocking rule has a high false-positive risk and the alternative is \"do it by manual review\", add a third tier: a nonblocking candidate-lint or surface-for-review tool. The \"no-tooling, just-review\" state silently leaks; the candidate tier is the durable middle."
      },
      "target_hooks": [
        {
          "target": "quality/validation_gate_config.md",
          "hook_type": "validation_gate_entry",
          "text": "Governed by operating principle OP-30 — see quality/rules_library.md."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-31",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "refactor-existing"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Refactoring",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "If two components seem consistent only because they never meet on the same path/key, unifying the path can activate a latent conflict. Don't just unify the reference — fix the ownership model so the conflict can't recur."
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-32",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "define+build"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Controls",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "When you add a validator or check, wire it into the actual workflow path the work passes through — a validator that exists but isn't called is a documentation artifact, not a control. Default to fail-closed on unknown inputs; silent pass-through is a leak."
      },
      "target_hooks": [
        {
          "target": "quality/validation_gate_config.md",
          "hook_type": "validation_gate_entry",
          "text": "Governed by operating principle OP-32 — see quality/rules_library.md."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-33",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "define+build"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Controls",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "When you classify something (a state / status / category), pair the label with an explicit action-when-this-fires. Passive labels without an action become ceremony; the operator sees the label and nothing happens. If you can't name the action, the classification isn't load-bearing."
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-34",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "markdown-CC"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "all-phases"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "applies-all",
      "authority_basis_default": "not_applicable",
      "authority_source_default": "not_applicable",
      "data_risk_gate": "n/a",
      "emission_posture": "install-verbatim",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Operator interaction",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "Whenever you give the operator a command, prompt, file path, or any verbatim block, present it so they can copy-paste without manual selection. For Claude-Code-based shapes that means a fenced code block. For other shapes, use the equivalent native UX. Never make the operator retype your output."
      },
      "target_hooks": [
        {
          "target": "agents/*_prompt.md",
          "hook_type": "agent_prompt_line",
          "text": "Governed by operating principle OP-34 — see quality/rules_library.md."
        },
        {
          "target": "CLAUDE.md",
          "hook_type": "cross_ref",
          "text": "Governed by operating principle OP-34 — see quality/rules_library.md."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_id": "OP-35",
      "cell_version": "1",
      "shape_scope": [
        "all-shapes"
      ],
      "phase_scope": [
        "define+build",
        "refactor-existing"
      ],
      "authority_gate": "high-risk-operator-approved",
      "authority_basis_default": "provisional_default",
      "authority_source_default": "wizard-default",
      "data_risk_gate": "data-class-conditional",
      "emission_posture": "shape-conditional",
      "public_source_label": "inherited operating principle",
      "applicability_gate": "has-public-distribution-surface = true",
      "realization": "corpus-body",
      "canonical": {
        "category": "Distribution boundary",
        "home": "quality/rules_library.md",
        "body": "If your system distributes artifacts publicly (releases, generated docs for end-users, etc.), every edit to a distributed artifact re-exposes the public boundary. Comments authored to document a fix can introduce a NEW leak. Store internal classification metadata in build-side sidecars, not in the distributed files. Run boundary-discipline checks at every edit, not just at release. (For operator systems WITHOUT a public-distribution surface, this principle is not applicable.)"
      },
      "target_hooks": [
        {
          "target": "quality/validation_gate_config.md",
          "hook_type": "validation_gate_entry",
          "text": "Governed by operating principle OP-35 — see quality/rules_library.md."
        }
      ]
    }
